Small business 
Part of the contributions, she says, was used to open a small business that she is currently running to fend for her family.
Ms Kitsao lost her husband in 2019 after he was attacked by criminal gangs in Kisauni Sub-county in Mombasa.
She also lost her last born in May this year, a week after she had received aid to save her children from starvation.
Her four-month-old baby, Mary Kaingu, died after having a fever for three days, she said.
To have a stable life, now Ms Kitsao says she will, together with her children, occupy three bedrooms in the new house which has a toilet and is connected to electricity.
The three other rooms, she says, will be rented out to allow her to have an income that she will use to take care of her seven children.

